01:24:03.680 --> 01:24:07.510
So today I hope we heard
native voices, native politics,

01:24:07.510 --> 01:24:11.370
native peoples
amplified at Harvard.

01:24:11.370 --> 01:24:15.230
And that by amplifying native
voices, Harvard and Radcliffe,

01:24:15.230 --> 01:24:19.430
again, to use the metaphor,
have been made more whole,

01:24:19.430 --> 01:24:22.040
if just for a day.

01:24:22.040 --> 01:24:23.540
And as we move
forward, I'm reminded

01:24:23.540 --> 01:24:27.090
of the daily work that
HUNAP, Shelly, and Dennis,

01:24:27.090 --> 01:24:30.930
and Jason, and Sam, and
others, and their students.

01:24:30.930 --> 01:24:33.960
The daily work that they
do in institutionalizing

01:24:33.960 --> 01:24:36.730
that native voice at Harvard.

01:24:36.730 --> 01:24:38.820
And I'm reminded that,
in order, for Harvard

01:24:38.820 --> 01:24:43.550
to be made whole in the future,
today's conversation needs

01:24:43.550 --> 01:24:49.230
to happen again, and
again, and again.

01:24:51.770 --> 01:24:53.580
In order for Harvard
to be made whole,

01:24:53.580 --> 01:24:58.000
the kinds of people you saw
today need to on our faculty.

